Some Results from the UNOS Data

Fan Wu

2016-11-09

Data Manipulation

We use the ESRD patients listed in 2006 from 41 U.S. states. The follow-up was untill Dec. 4, 2015. The time origin is set at the ESRD onset, which is the date of the first regulatory dialysis. The event of interest is patient death. We exclude those

  • without a dialysis date
  • put on the waiting list with out reaching ESRD (defined by starting dialysis)
  • have unknow dialysis modality before listed

We allow the renal replacement therapy of a patient change during the follow up, from dialysis to TX after receiving an allograft, or from TX to dialysis following the allograft failure and he/her is on dialysis again. Thus, the treatment is treated as a time-dependent covariate.

We also adjusted for age at ESRD onset, gender and race.

The number of events for each included states are as follows:

To Make the Analysis Great Again

I may

  • Include the cohort of the ESRD patient to adjusted for possible cohort effect
  • Categorize the continuous AGE0 variable to <45, 45-64, 65+ to allow for non-linear age effect
  • Change the time point of switching the “on-going” treatment (e.g., 60 days after the switch)
